<a name="4"></a>
<h4><span>4. </span>General Conditions</h4>

<ul class="toc">
	<li>The Event is open only to persons aged 18 years or over at the time of admission.</li>
	<li>Proof of age will be required. This is in the form of the University Card or in the case of Non-University Guests photographic ID in the form of a Passport or Driving License.</li>
	<li>We reserve the right to refuse admission to the Event, for any reason, at Our sole discretion.</li>
	<li>No alcoholic drinks may be brought into the event.</li>
	<li>We reserve the right to ask Security to search anybody who We suspect may be attempting to do so.</li>
	<li>Any Guest found or suspected to be in possession of an illegal substance will be removed from the Event and their personal details passed on to the police.</li>
	<li>Should We or Security deem necessary, due to unacceptable behaviour or otherwise, Guests may be removed from the Event.</li>
	<li>You are responsible for the behaviour of Your Non-University Guests at all times during the Event. Should this be deemed unacceptable then disciplinary procedures may be taken against You as appropriate. If You are required to leave the event then so will Your Non-University Guests.</li>
	<li>Any damage caused to College property, by You or Your Guests, whether accidental or otherwise, will be billed to You.</li>
	<li>We reserve the right to contact your college, department or the relevant law enforcement authorities to request aid in enforcing these Terms & Conditions.</li>
	<li>Any advertised acts, features or facilities are representative of the current plans for the Event, but may be subject to change. Changes will not be considered cause for refund.</li>
	<li>No refunds will be given where a Guest has been ejected or refused admission to the Event for breaking these Terms & Conditions.</li>
	<li>Refunds will not be issued where the Event is cancelled, or does not run for the advertised length of time, due to circumstances out of Our control.</li>
	<li>By attending the event you agree for any photographs or video/audio recordings that are made of You to be used by Us for promotional purposes.</li>
</ul>

<a name="5"></a>
<h4><span>5. </span>Ticket Conditions</h4>

<ul class="toc">
	<li>There are two types of ticket available; Standard and QueueJump.</li>
	<li>Standard tickets cost &pound;70 per person for King&rsquo;s College Members and &pound;85 per person for Non-King&rsquo;s College Members and entitle holders to enter the Event at 9.00pm.</li>
	<li>QueueJump tickets are an extra &pound;10 per person upgrade and entitle holders to enter the Event at 9.00pm before standard ticket holders.</li>
	<li>Members of King&rsquo;s College can purchase a ticket for themselves and two guests who must be bona fide acquaintance of the Principal Ticket Holder, but need not be connected with the University of Cambridge.</li>
	<li>All tickets are non-transferable. If a Guest arrives with a ticket that does not match their identification then they will be refused entry. For legal reasons this rule will be strictly enforced.</li>
	<li>Tickets are non-refundable once purchased. A small number of refunds may be issued in exceptional circumstances at the discretion of the Chair. Requests must be submitted in writing using the contact details on this website. In this case an administrative charge of &pound;10 will be levied.</li>
	<li>We will only allow changes to the Principal Ticket Holder in exceptional circumstances at the discretion of the Chair. Requests must be submitted in writing using the contact details on This Website. In this case an administrative charge at the discretion of the Chair will be levied.</li>
	<li>Changes to the names of Your Guest can be processed online. Name changes can be made for a limited period of time for free until 9pm on 1<sup>st</sup> March, at a cost of &pound;10 per name change until 9pm on Tuesday 1<sup>st</sup> April. Thereafter name changes will cost &pound;20 each until 9pm on Thursday 1<sup>st</sup> May. Thereafter name changes will cost &pound;30 per name change and can be made up until 11pm on Monday 16<sup>th</sup> June. Changes will not be reflected on actual tickets but on our electronic records.</li>
	<li>Such changes must be settled by a Bank Transfer from the Principal Ticket Holder.</li>
	<li>Tickets must be collected during the advertised ticket collection times, otherwise they may face automatic and non-refundable cancellation. If You are unable to attend any of the ticket collection sessions You must inform Us immediately.</li>
	<li>Tickets can be collected by the Principal Ticket Holder only, except with prior agreement of the Chair.</li>
	<li>In order to be admitted to the event, tickets must be kept in good condition and must not be defaced in any way.</li>
	<li>We reserve the right to refuse any name change or cancellation request, or alter the applicable administration charges, should we feel necessary. No changes will be made after tickets have been collected.</li>
	<li>Orders must be paid for within the time limits and in accordance with the instructions specified on This Website. Admission will be refused to any Guests where the payment for their ticket has not been settled.</li>
	<li>We reserve the right to cancel and refund any order up to the time of ticket collection.</li>
</ul>

