<a name="7"></a>
<h4><span>7. </span>Privacy Policy</h4>

<p>By visiting this website and completing the Raven authentication process, you agree to your information being stored in a database, for the purpose of administering ticket sales.</p>
<p>Information on You, and Your Guests, may be automatically retrieved from the University&rsquo;s Hermes email directory, for the purposes of simplifying the purchase process.</p>
<p>You agree to us using the supplied CRSIDs, email addresses, and/or college information to contact you about the ticketing process, or about other events which you may be interested in.</p>
<p>Your information will not be passed to any other parties, except where required by law, for the processing of payments, or for audit purposes.</p>
<p>This is in accordance with the 1998 Data Protection Act.</p>
<p>You have the right to ask for a copy of the information we hold about you and to ask for any errors to be corrected. To do this please contact, <a href="webmaster@kingsaffair.com">webmaster@kingsaffair.com</a>.</p>
<p>Your information will be stored, and passed to future King&rsque;s Affair Committees, for up to five years, after which it may be used for statistical analysis once anonymised.</p>

<a name="8"></a>
<h4><span>8. </span>Equality</h4>
<p>King&rsquo;s Affair has a policy of trying to make the Event accessible to all members of the University, regardless of any disabilities or medical conditions.</p>
<p>It is, however, essential that you inform us as soon as you purchase your ticket, if you have any such conditions so that we can cater appropriately for them.</p>
<p>This can be done by emailing <a href="webmaster@kingsaffair.com">webmaster@kingsaffair.com</a>.</p>

